id: automation/codex-repo-agent
title: "codex repo agent"
kind: automation-agent
status: v0-seed
updated: 2026-07-01

purpose: >
  Define the Codex-side agent posture for helping maintain the .yawn open-source
  repository.

may:
  - inspect GitHub issues and pull requests
  - inspect local .yawn files
  - classify feedback to nodes
  - propose bounded changes
  - draft patch plans

must_not_without_approval:
  - push commits
  - create releases
  - merge pull requests
  - modify secrets
  - send email
  - write to the database

identity_note: >
  Do not use a personal GitHub identity as a hidden bot. For durable automation,
  prefer a GitHub App or a dedicated bot/service account such as yawn-agent,
  clearly labeled as automation.

proof:
  source:
    - agents/contributor-agent.yawn
    - automation/github-feedback-triage.yawn
  status: seed-backed
